Male genitalia.
Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view sickle-shaped, narrowing in apical third to skewed, dorsally slightly extended apex; in 2/3 of its length with small tooth on ventral side (
Fig. 33
). Parameres moderately broad, ‘C’-shaped; apex short and broad; apical lobes long, club-shaped (
Fig. 34
).
